Here we are accepting any function type, even methods where the `this` context is expected to be set.  Note that I&#39;m consistently using [rest tuple types](https://github.com/Microsoft/TypeScript/wiki/What&#39;s-new-in-TypeScript#tuples-in-rest-parameters-and-spread-expressions) to represent the list of arguments.  The type of `arguments` isn&#39;t very strong in TypeScript, probably because for ES2015+ code you should be using rest parameters anyway.  Anyway, the return type of `once()` is a function with the same `this` context and parameter list as `fn`, and with the same return type or `undefined`.  This typing should mostly work for you, I think:

